children.text: The wall and penetrations above the basin/trough have not been waterproofed to 150mm in accordance with the Building Code of Australia (BCA) and relevant Australian Standard AS 3740 to prevent water leaks into the structure that could cause damage.
Part 3.8.1.2 of the Building Code of Australia (NCC/BCA) - Wet Areas, states that;
‘Building elements in wet areas within a building must-
be waterproof or water resistant in accordance with Table 3.8.1.1; and
Table 3.8.1.1 in the NCC/BCA shows that the wall over the vessel must be water resistant to 150mm high, and any penetrations that occur in the water resistant surfaces are required to be waterproof;
The builder must install waterproofing to 150mm high around the basin/trough and around the penetrations as required by the NCC’s Building Code of Australia and Australian Standard AS 3740.
